Don't forget to bring your laptops. We have some cools stickers!

events.name: Study Jam - Orchestration: Bootstrapping the app (1/3)

venue.name: Dutch Hub - Your Coworking Space in Tirana

events.description:
Container orchestration is the automatic process of managing or scheduling the work of individual containers for applications based on microservices within multiple clusters. The widely deployed container orchestration platforms are based on open-source versions like Kubernetes, Docker Swarm or the commercial version from Red Hat OpenShift.

In this series of Study Jam, we will learn how to build and split a monolith into smaller, more maintainable & scalable apps following microservice principles and deployment using various orchestration platforms.

Bootstrapping the app:
- Setup a simple blog app with NodeJs & MongoDB (with Mongoose ORM).
- Setup Google Cloud Container
- Test & Deploy app
- Introduce Microservice Patterns
- Ready for Study Jam 2!!

Drinks, Snacks, Chit-Chat

P.s. Bring your laptops!

events.name: Destroy boilerplate code with Android Architecture Components
events.description:
An introduction to Android Architecture Components.
Speaker: Stavro Xhardha

What to expect?
Exploring one of Androids Jetpack most important element, Architecture Components.
A comparison of MVVM and MVP architecture, and how to utilize Arch Components.
What are some valuable libraries and how to use them in production?

Questions and discussions at the end of the event.

events.name: What if ... i18n in Angular could be easier?
events.description:
What a better way to start the New Year than talking about the cutting edge features that were released most recently. We have invited Isuert Majlti, Frontend Engineer @Backbase, Amsterdam, to show us how to have a multi-language application in Angular.

After the talk, we introduce to the community our goals for the new year, how we did in 2019 and we have prepared a small surprise for our members.

Agenda:
18:30 - 19:00: Networking
19:00 - 19:30: Angular Talk - I.Mjalti
19:30 - 19:45: Community & 2019 Honorary Members - E.Mamoci
19:45: Networking - Food & Drinks

Hope to see you soon!

* The talk will be held in Albanian language

events.name: Using ML and AI to power your Images
events.description:
OFICINA and Google Developer Group Tirana are hosting a great meetup on the 30th of January with three excellent speakers lecturing a the hottest topics in tech.
Doug Sillers, authorO’Reilly’s “High Performance Android Apps” and a google developer expert, Mr. Ville Korpela is a Founding Partner of Helsinki based Impact Innovation Institute Oy Ltd, which specialises on innovation funding and growth strategies of radical AI/ML assisted innovations globally and
Besnik Hajredini a serial entrepreneur, founder of tepazari.com and organiser of #GDG Prishtine.

Topics to be discussed:
1- Ways to use AI and ML to perform object detection and improve the images on your website.
2- Market opportunities and access to funding for AI/ML startups and entrepreneurs
3- Google AI/ML usage | Case from Kosova Startup Tepazari.com
